<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1580,1930]" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">
In the year 1861, Mitten described 
<taxonomicName authority="Mitten (1861: 103)" authorityName="Mitten" authorityPageNumber="103" authorityYear="1861" box="[522,940,1618,1642]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lepidoziaceae" genus="Lepidozia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis box="[522,725,1618,1642]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Lepidozia flexuosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mitten, W." box="[733,940,1618,1642]" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" pagination="89 - 128" refId="ref2054" refString="Mitten, W. (1861) Hepaticae Indiae Orientalis. Journal of the Proceedings of the Linnean Society. Botany 5: 89 - 128. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8312.1860. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1861">Mitten (1861: 103)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
based on specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[1234,1311,1618,1642]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
collected by 
<emphasis box="[136,281,1654,1678]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">
<collectionCode box="[136,150,1654,1678]" country="South Africa" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14647" name="University of the Witwatersrand" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">J</collectionCode>
.D.H[ooker]
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[298,430,1654,1678]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">1411, 1411b</emphasis>
), from Khasia mountains [now 
<collectingRegion box="[779,900,1654,1678]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
] collected by 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">
<collectionCode box="[1054,1068,1654,1678]" country="South Africa" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14647" name="University of the Witwatersrand" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">J</collectionCode>
.D.H[ooker] &amp; 
<collectionCode box="[1237,1253,1655,1678]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">T</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode box="[1264,1280,1654,1678]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">T</collectionCode>
[homson] 1415, 1456
</emphasis>
and from 
<collectingRegion box="[305,378,1690,1714]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Assam</collectingRegion>
by 
<emphasis box="[421,574,1690,1714]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">
<collectionCode box="[421,443,1690,1714]" country="Austria" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15588" name="Naturhistorisches Museum Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">W</collectionCode>
.Griffith s.n.
</emphasis>
but without designating a 
<typeStatus box="[868,917,1690,1714]" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">type</typeStatus>
. On examination of the images of the specimens housed at 
<collectionCode box="[243,281,1726,1749]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
, I found 
<specimenCount box="[374,521,1726,1750]" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="generic">two specimen</specimenCount>
packets of 
<collectionCode box="[642,654,1726,1749]" country="South Africa" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14647" name="University of the Witwatersrand" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">J</collectionCode>
.D. Hooker’s labelled 1411: one from 
<collectingRegion box="[1055,1132,1726,1750]" country="India" name="Sikkim" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Sikkim</collectingRegion>
Himalaya [now 
<collectingRegion box="[1308,1445,1726,1750]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
] Tonglo [=Tonglu], 
<quantity box="[340,444,1762,1786]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.048" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" unit="ft" value="10000.0">10,000 ft.</quantity>
with (Barcode 
<collectionCode box="[609,648,1762,1786]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
00236759) (
<figureCitation box="[778,850,1762,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE A" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1102,1124]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-15@1.[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE A. 1. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760); 2. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760) showing entire population (enlarged). ©Copyright of the Board of Trustees of the New York Botanical Garden, New York." pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Fig. A</figureCitation>
1 top right-hand side; 
<figureCitation box="[1083,1151,1762,1786]" captionStart="FIGURE A" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1102,1124]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-15@1.[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE A. 1. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760); 2. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760) showing entire population (enlarged). ©Copyright of the Board of Trustees of the New York Botanical Garden, New York." pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Fig. A</figureCitation>
2 top left-hand side) and the other from Sinchul [=Senchal], 
<quantity box="[475,565,1798,1822]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1336" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" unit="ft" value="7000.0">7,000 ft.</quantity>
with barcode (
<collectionCode box="[723,762,1798,1822]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
00236760) (
<figureCitation box="[893,965,1798,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE A" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1102,1124]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-15@1.[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE A. 1. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760); 2. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760) showing entire population (enlarged). ©Copyright of the Board of Trustees of the New York Botanical Garden, New York." pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Fig. A</figureCitation>
1 bottom right-hand side; 
<figureCitation box="[1238,1305,1798,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE A" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1102,1124]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-15@1.[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE A. 1. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760); 2. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760) showing entire population (enlarged). ©Copyright of the Board of Trustees of the New York Botanical Garden, New York." pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Fig. A</figureCitation>
2 bottom lefthand side). The other Hooker specimen mentioned in the protologue, 1411b (Barcode 
<collectionCode box="[1077,1116,1834,1858]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
00236761) (
<collectionCode box="[1248,1289,1834,1858]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
) was collected from Nongkli, 
<collectingRegion box="[297,373,1870,1894]" country="India" name="Assam" pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Assam</collectingRegion>
. (
<figureCitation box="[392,465,1870,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE A" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1102,1124]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-15@1.[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE A. 1. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760); 2. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760) showing entire population (enlarged). ©Copyright of the Board of Trustees of the New York Botanical Garden, New York." pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Fig. A</figureCitation>
1 bottom left-hand side; 
<figureCitation box="[730,799,1870,1894]" captionStart="FIGURE A" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1102,1124]" captionTargetBox="[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetId="figure-15@1.[165,1422,188,1076]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE A. 1. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760); 2. Lectotype of Lepidozia flexuosa Mitt. (India, Sikkim [West Bengal], Sinchul [Senchal], J.D. Hooker 1411, NY00236760) showing entire population (enlarged). ©Copyright of the Board of Trustees of the New York Botanical Garden, New York." pageId="0" pageNumber="217">Fig. A</figureCitation>
2 middle right hand side) All other specimens mentioned by Mitten in his protologue were not located at 
<collectionCode box="[610,647,1906,1929]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15556" name="William and Lynda Steere Herbarium of the New York Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="217" type="Herbarium">NY</collectionCode>
(Laura Briscoe 
